  • Interface Summary
    Interface
    Description
    _IOperator
    Represents a class which can represents an instruction
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    ADD
    ADD replaces the B-target with the sum of the A-value and the B-value
    CMP
    CMP compares two instructions, and skips the next instruction if they are equal
    DAT
    No additional processing takes place.
    DIV
    DIV replaces the B-target with the integral result of dividing the B-value by the A-value
    DJN
    DJN decrements a number by one, and jumps unless the result is 0
    JMN
    tests a number and jumps if it is not 0
    JMP
    JMP queues the sum of the program counter and the A-pointer.
    JMZ
    JMZ tests a number and jumps to an address if it is 0
    LDP
    LDP loads a number from private storage space
    MOD
    MOD replaces the B-target with the integral remainder of dividing the B-value by the A-value
    MOV
    MOV replaces the B-target with the A-value
    MUL
    MUL replaces the B-target with the product of the A-value and the B-value
    NOP
    No operation takes place.
    SEQ
    SEQ compares two instructions, and skips the next instruction if they are equal
    SLT
    SLT compares two values, and skips the next instruction if the first is lower than the second
    SNE
    SNE compares two instructions, and skips the next instruction if they are equa
    SPL
    SPL queues the next instruction and then queues the sum of the program counter and A-pointer.
    STP
    STP saves a number to private storage space
    SUB
    SUB replaces the B-target with the difference of the B-value and the A-value
